+ Show that, for any set $A$, $A \cup A = A \cup \phi = \phi \cup A = A$.

Hypothesis:

$$
  \begin{align}
    \forall x, x \in A = A \tag 0 \\
    \forall x, x \in A \cup B \leftrightarrow x \in A \vee x \in B \tag 1 \\
    \forall x, x \not\in \phi \tag 2
  \end{align}
$$

Proof:

$$
  \begin{align*}
    A \cup A & \leftrightarrow \forall x, x \in A \cup A & \textrm{by (1)} \\
             & \leftrightarrow \forall x, x \in A = A & \textrm{by (0)} \\
    A \cup \phi & \leftrightarrow \forall x, x \in A \vee x \in \phi & \textrm{by (1)} \\
                & \leftrightarrow \forall x, x \in A = A & \textrm{by (2), intuition, and (0)} \\
    \phi \cup A & = A & \textrm{by similar argument}
  \end{align*}
$$

